    "body": "I can reproduce on macOS 10.12.3, electron 1.6.2.\r\n\r\nI modified the repro case to make it possible to simply paste it into the console of an existing view:\r\n\r\n```js\r\ndocument.body.innerHTML = '<h1>Put cursor over me</h1>'\r\nsetInterval(function() {\r\n  var h1 = document.querySelector('h1');\r\n  if (h1.style.cursor == 'wait') {\r\n    h1.style.cursor = '';\r\n  } else {\r\n    h1.style.cursor = 'wait';\r\n  }\r\n}, 1000);\r\n```\r\n\r\nPasting this into a HTML page running in Chrome 57 works as expected â€” every second the cursor switches between \"wait\" and default.\r\n\r\nHowever, pasting this into a `<webview>` of the Figma electron app doesn't, unless I continuously move the mouse.\r\n\r\nWould be really really great to fix this."
